    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-02-07T16:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-02-07T16:36:00-05:00" n="614"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/344: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-02-07T15:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1920—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 8—4:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. British and French representatives here and many Americans and other
                    nationals conferred with me about disturbed conditions, numerous arrests, and
                    danger of bloodshed.</p>
                <p>Realizing their fears not without foundation I obtained interview with the
                    President February 5th laying before him the situation deferentially but
                    directly. His reception and manner were cordial but he had not before realized
                    the magnitude, apparently, of the opposition to his regime; situation somewhat
                    improved. Department’s 8<note n="3" xml:id="d614fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> potent for good.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
